Singapore Stocks: Portek International, Tiger Air, Yongnam

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   B u r g o s
-- 
2011-05-20T09:56:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-20/singapore-stocks-portek-international-tiger-air-yongnam.html
Singapore’s  Straits Times Index (FSSTI) 
dropped 0.1 percent to 3,168.54 at the close. The gauge climbed
0.2 percent this week. About the same number of stocks fell and
rose on the benchmark index of 30 companies.  Shares on the measure trade at an average 14.6 times
estimated earnings, compared with about 15.6 times at the end of
2010, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  The following shares were among the most active in the
market. Stock symbols are in parentheses after the company name.  Portek International Ltd. (PORT)  , a Singapore-based port
operator and supplier of container cranes, advanced 3.3 percent
to 77.5 Singapore cents. The company said it has a “healthy”
order book, totaling S$44 million ($35.6 million) as of May 1.  Tiger Airways Holdings Ltd. (TGR)  , the budget carrier
partly-owned by Singapore Airlines Ltd. (SIA SP), slipped 1.3
percent to S$1.53. Tiger Air said fourth-quarter net income fell
to S$1.3 million from S$22.3 million a year earlier. Separately,
the company said it signed a term sheet for the purchase of a 33
percent stake in Indonesia’s PT Mandala Airlines.  Yongnam Holdings Ltd. (YNH)  , a Singapore-based
construction company, increased 2 percent to 26 Singapore cents.
The company said it won a contract, valued at S$50 million, for
the supply of structural steel to be used in the restoration of
the old Supreme Court and City Hall buildings in the city.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan Burgos in  Singapore  at 
 jburgos4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Gentle at   ngentle2@bloomberg.net . 